operating expense was virtually flat to 2001, despite higher expenses related
to acquisitions. during 2002, t&ss achieved expense reductions through
productivity and quality initiatives, including six sigma and selected staff
reductions. in addition, investor services restructured its expense base in
response to the weak revenue environment. despite low revenue growth, the
overhead ratio for t&ss was 74%, compared with 76% in 2001.
