(a)
corporate/reconciling items includes support units, corporate and the net
effect of management accounting policies.
(b)
equity-related income includes equity income of investees accounted for by
the equity method.
(c)
intersegment revenue includes intercompany revenue and revenue-sharing
agreements, net of intersegment expenses. transactions between business
segments are primarily conducted at fair value.
(d)
represents the after-tax amounts.
(e)
includes credit card receivables that have been securitized. the impact of
securitizations on total average assets was $26.5billion in
2002, $18.0billion
in 2001 and $18.8billion in 2000.
