(a)
all nonperforming loans accounted for on a nonaccrual basis. there were no
nonperforming renegotiated loans. renegotiated loans are those for which
concessions, such as the reduction of interest rates or the deferral of
interest or principal payments, have been granted as a result of a
deterioration in the borrowers financial condition.
